\multicolumn{2}{r}{x^4} & +2x^3 & -x^2 \\
\cline{2-4}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & -2x^3 & +4x^2 & -7x \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & -2x^3 & -4x^2 & +2x \\
\cline{3-5}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & +8x^2 & -9x & \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} &  & +8x^2 & +16x & -8 \\
\cline{4-6}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} &  &  & -25x & +8 \\
\end{array}
\]Thus, the quotient is $\boxed{x^2 - 2x + 8}.$

By the Triangle Inequality,
\[|w| = |(w - z) + z| \le |w - z| + |z|,\]so $|w - z| \le |w| - |z| = 5 - 2 = 3.$

We can achieve this bound by taking $w = 5$ and $z = 2,$ so the smallest possible value is $\boxed{3}.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.5 cm);

